As Matthew wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/22/2004 at 20:55:28 (Eastern Time),
>Sorry to bother you again, but I am not sure if my solution is 
>correct. I checked my solution with a spreadsheet, and got a 
>slightly different answer. It may be because the fractions become so 
>small that the computer does not compute sufficient decimal places. 
>Unfortunately, i can not attach the spreadsheet to this email.
>
>Using the formula, after cancelling i got:
>
>1 + (1)/(2^2) - (1)/((1000)^2) - (1)/((1001)^2)
>= 5/4 - 0.000001 - 0.000000998002996
>=approx. 1.249998001997004
>
>Which must be divided by 4:
>
>so = 0.3124995
>
>So, what is the correct answer? Should it be expressed in decimal or 
>fraction form?

The answer you got from the formula is correct, so there must be some roundoff 
error in the spreadsheet result.  If you want to express the answer exactly, you should 
write it as a fraction; if you just need a certain number of decimal places, then the 
decimal form is fine.


